{"word":"ἀναπίπτω","slug":"ἀναπίπτω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀναπίπτω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνά\">ἀνά</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πέμπω\">πέμπω</a></el>; <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prim.\">prim.</a> ‘fall back’ then ‘recline’, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> at meals] <b><i>recline</i></b> for a meal <b><a href='B:480 6:40'>Mk 6:40</a>; <a href='B:490 11:37'>Lk 11:37</a>; <a href='B:500 13:12'>J 13:12</a>.</b> In <b>13:25</b> the apostle who reclines in a position of honor next to Jesus <i>leans back</i> (here <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀναπίπτω\">ἀναπίπτω</a></el> approaches the primary sense ‘fall back’). <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναπηδάω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναπληρόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}